<TITLE> Syria accepts invitation to Annapolis conference </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 DAMASCUS, Nov 25 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Syria on Sunday accepted a US invitation to a peace conference in Annapolis and named Deputy Foreign Minister Fayssal al-Mekdad as head of its delegation. The official news agency said Syria had decided to go after receiving a copy of the agenda stating there would be a session on reviving Syrian-Israeli peace talks. An earlier round of such talks, focused on normalising ties in return for Israel returning the Golan Heights to Syria, collapsed in 2000. "The government of the Syrian Arab Republic has accepted the American invitation," the agency said. Syria had said it would not attend unless the Golan Heights, which Israel occupied 1967, were on the agenda. A diplomat said the copy of the agenda delivered by the US embassy to the Syrian Foreign Ministry on Sunday had a sub-heading referring to the Syrian-Israeli track under a session about comprehensive Middle East pea
